<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="material">White marble</rs> <rs reg="sarcophagus" type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">2.66</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.19</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">1.36</measure>: interior <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">2.15</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.87</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">1.00</measure>).  The front face has an elaborately carved <rs type="decoration">garland</rs> running along the upper edge and part-way down the two sides, and a simple moulding below. On the face busts, a <rs type="decoration">bearded male</rs> (to the left) and a <rs type="decoration">veiled female</rs> (to the right), are carved in relief profile, facing one another, each on a rectangular pedestal, with moulding above and below. See further Smith (below)</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>The texts are <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">inscribed</rs> on the face to the left of the male bust (i); between the two (ii) and to the right of the female bust (iii).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p>i: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.03</measure>; ii: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.0225-0.025</measure>; iii: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02-0.025</measure>.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
 <head>Date</head>

<p><date notBefore="0161" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Late second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">sculpture</rs>).</p></div>

